Issues.Body:
### Description

The new control flow is great. There are some users, like myself that find it a little messier looking, specifically the extra indentation, and braces. It makes it look more of a jumble of html and JS. I think a lot of users liked the fact that the templates looked like plain html using the old *ng directives. I understand the old syntax is still available. A solution would add an alternate short hand control flow  that utilizes html's existing indentation and block scope ( open/close tag). This will be most useful for small control flow one liners. 

### Proposed solution

This proposal does not change existing control flow. It adds a shorthand alternative. It allows control flow @ syntax to be used in html tags, and scope is determined by the tags open/close tags. 
 
  ``` 
<div @if(person1)>{{person1.name}}, {{person1.name}}</div>
<div @if(person2)>{{person2.name}}, {{person2.name}}</div>
<div @if(person3)>{{person3.name}}, {{person3.name}}</div>
``` 

### Alternatives considered

Alternatively use the old syntax

```
@if (person1) {
  <div>{{person1.name}}, {{person1.name}}</div>
}
@if (person2) {
  <div>{{person2.name}}, {{person2.name}}</div>
}
@if (person3) {
  <div>{{person3.name}}, {{person3.name}}</div>
}
```

### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core, Don't known / other

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

Hi there!
I've faced with strange issue.

Look, I have the app-table component which was created as a base table of the application.
Also, I have the patients-table component that inherits the app-table.

The problem is with paginator and sort, when I'm trying to refreshGrid.

There is a base component - patients. It has a two components inside it - patients-options-panel and patients-table.
I'm trying to call refreshGrid method with filters of the patients-options-panel inside patients component.

It successfully calls that method, but paginator and sort members are undefined. Why? It shoulda been initialized in the parent component - app-table. What am I doing wrong?

Also, using Chrome DevTools I see that we are in the PatientsTableComponent when I click search in options panel. And sort with paginator isn't defined here. This is really upsets me.

